[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing library overrides**\n\nI’m noticing that AndroidLibrary has an isProvided override feature. SimpleLibrary could potentially have isProvided set to false, but then there's SimpleJavaLibrary that overrides this. If AndroidLibrary is marked as optional and set to true, it makes sense that isProvided should align with the optional status. I wonder if maintaining consistency between these is critical for functionality. There’s a lot of detail here to digest!\n\n**Reviewing library behavior**\n\nI'm looking into the SimpleLibrary issues and how SimpleAndroidLibrary doesn't override correctly. It seems the assert might not be working as expected. There's also this ambiguity with the provided flag, which should be optional. It's better to ensure that SimpleAndroidLibrary's isProvided correctly reflects this. I need to add some assertions for Android to clarify things further. Then, I'll implement the necessary changes, including importing the TestedTargetVariant for proper functionality. Time to edit!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e57c24e4f3260300169fa515edfb481948afd19bc1b017d16\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-lFp9KP0678_yWA2VB4RDFfpWftVsSqXqXHlpDHidE3-qOlNWVRWgZvw2mIc92Pcgi98enw05QC_fl30D3lSTg5Y9h1MPDXhmHvfku4xdlwZaID4bvkUh5Ry2_9kFRy2ovv6-CWd_F-b4Pb7Ah-vr09530QoZrUEpZj9J-GFNn9N2PdcAvIcJxCfh6eykwCXGERlQw1a5vqWW41ZqdcieTAQyp8Y-gClVTFusgy0i3UC1zflLxeJPCT_q7iB9WPp60FAk7hmaFX0qfQ6CIGrU7UCtzbNAN55Bh-fz98HZcmZS5QXRa3CQMFiz2-d7A6I4Qnl7iNuiDC9BzY0dcnmQCbm1---IO0aWs54vwt3vFQGDuZvWSJe7USp0gyeNaLCw5FCx2kZ0cMBf7C5_DzDf9lap9HTu11pWxDsJ7nbtmSVud4d8WvWRX2_882Sj3li1XdIp3p_zypJW0QxtkgAYTaDDkOHma54it16wIAbtupcoFMIZCQ_LBLfM5WH_lNWbmD9OWb06POkyjIcv6ZG178QSvvfbSfj3_Di9VEsC2xyHNIgbxt2gyhZbIvManCC_EVa0RL_kv6OTiDHVLV0G2O7FfVMSXHy_VRNtzdyGH5YqOhDuhVIU99Qqogk-2O-dsjVFMM-aNPfffLHBLi4QEP431zmTEESJv0FYCXKo37vmECSy8yGRX8Ug4mkf_YfFONkMvA4VyVh8SciCvDb